    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Bulgogi</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 pound thinly sliced beef (ribeye or sirloin)</li>
            <li>1/2 cup soy sauce</li>
            <li>3 tablespoons brown sugar</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons mirin (sweet rice wine)</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon sesame oil</li>
            <li>3 cloves garlic, minced</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon grated ginger</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons pear juice (or grated pear)</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons finely chopped green onions</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon sesame seeds</li>
            <li>Vegetable oil for cooking</li>
            <li>Optional: Sliced mushrooms and onions for stir-frying</li>
            <li>Steamed rice for serving</li>
            <li>Lettuce leaves for wrapping (optional)</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Bulgogi</li>
            <li>Korean</li>
            <li>Beef</li>
            <li>Stir-fry</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a bowl, whisk together soy sauce, brown sugar, mirin, sesame oil, minced garlic, grated ginger, pear juice, green onions, and sesame seeds to create the marinade.</li>
            <li>Place the thinly sliced beef in a resealable plastic bag or shallow dish and pour the marinade over it. Ensure the beef is well coated, then refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to marinate.</li>
            <li>Heat vegetable oil in a pan over medium-high heat. Add the marinated beef and stir-fry until cooked through and caramelized.</li>
            <li>If desired, add sliced mushrooms and onions to the pan and stir-fry until they are tender.</li>
            <li>Serve the bulgogi over steamed rice. Optionally, you can use lettuce leaves to wrap the bulgogi, creating wraps.</li>
            <li>Garnish with additional green onions and sesame seeds if desired.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your delicious Bulgogi!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

